HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 694
By Doggett
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Benjamin and Lauren
Neale upon their receipt of the Rural Small
Business of the Year award.
WHEREAS, small businesses are the backbone of Tennessee's economy, and the
goods and services provided by their diligent proprietors contribute significantly to the overall
well-being of the citizens of this State; and
WHEREAS, such estimable small business owners are Benjamin and Lauren Neale,
owners of Light Hill Meats, who were awarded the Rural Small Business of the Year award by
the United States Small Business Administration's Tennessee District Office; and
WHEREAS, Benjamin Neale was raised on a small farm in Lynnville, where he worked
for neighboring farmers and seedstock operations; he earned an undergraduate degree in
animal science and master's degrees in agricultural operations and business administration;
and
WHEREAS, Mr. Neale, who began building his cow herd in 2011, officially opened the
doors to Light Hill Meats in 2017, and has since grown the family enterprise into an integrated
farm-to-table beef business with a deep commitment to the community; and
WHEREAS, today, Light Hill Meats includes a cow-calf herd, a USDA-inspected
processing facility for cattle, pigs, sheep, and goats, and a retail butcher shop that serves
families throughout Middle Tennessee; and
WHEREAS, Light Hill Meats Butcher Shop features local beef and pork, as well as
seafood and chicken, and specializes in a fourteen-day dry hang process to enhance the meat's
tenderness and flavor; and
