WHEREAS, during the COVID-19 pandemic, Lauren Neale identified a need for
supplying meat to concerned parents in the community; the Neales launched a pop-up shop at
first and in 2022, began construction for a retail location in Spring Hill; and
WHEREAS, Light Hill Meats Custom Processing operates out of Lynnville, and the
facility services both the USDA and custom processing of cattle, sheep, and pigs; and
WHEREAS, leaders in their profession and the community, Benjamin and Lauren Neale
care deeply about leaving a positive impact on the lives of citizens and their employees and
often host creative events for special needs children and support organizations for autism and
sober living; and
WHEREAS, their professional accomplishments aside, Benjamin and Lauren Neale are
the proud parents of four children: Corban, Abigail, Elizabeth, and Sarah; and
WHEREAS, it is most fitting that we join in acknowledging these exceptional Tennessee
entrepreneurs; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we congratulate Benjamin and Lauren Neale upon their receipt of the
Rural Small Business of the Year award from the U.S. Small Business Administration's
Tennessee District Office, extending our best wishes for much continued success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
